commit.message:
Update dnsmap.c

Fix dnsmap for TLDs longer than 6 characters (like .network.)  There are many TLDs above 6 characters these days.  The longest English TLD is 18 chars, the longest global TLD is 24 chars. 
 I stopped at 13 characters because most of the TLDs longer than 13 chars are ridiculous and I think dnsmap has a brute force feature for TLDs.  This seems outdated because you can find all accepted TLDs on Mozilla's PublicSuffix list.
